The next step is to make sure BBs or pellets will not bounce off any surface and hit you. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/77/Have-Fun-With-an-Air-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Have-Fun-With-an-Air-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/77/Have-Fun-With-an-Air-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid267307-v4-728px-Have-Fun-With-an-Air-Gun-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
